Ladies and gentlemen, football aficionados from around the world! Get ready for a challenge that will test your knowledge of the greatest teams in World Cup history. Your task is to create a function that will take an array of team names and return an object. This object will have each team name as a key and the number of World Cups they've won as the value. Let's dive into the data of champions and see who comes out on top!

## World Cup Data

Here's the chronological data for the World Cup winners:

```javascript
const worldCupWinners = [
  "Uruguay", "Italy", "Italy", "Uruguay", "Germany", 
  "Brazil", "Brazil", "England", "Brazil", "Germany", 
  "Argentina", "Italy", "Argentina", "Germany", 
  "Brazil", "France", "Brazil", "Italy", "Spain", 
  "Germany", "France", "Argentina"
];
```

## Example

```javascript
const teams = ["Brazil", "Germany", "Argentina"];
console.log(worldCupWins(teams));
// Output: { Brazil: 5, Germany: 4, Argentina: 3 }
```
